<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">883.0513/163: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-09T17:00:00-04:00">July 9, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>25. Your 40, July 8, noon. The Department is disposed to refrain from
                            pressing the matter at this time provided the entire question can <pb facs="0081" n="16" xml:id="pg_16"/> be held in abeyance until Judge
                            Booth’s return. However, if the question is likely to be presented to
                            the Council of Ministers for a decision in the near future the
                            Department would desire to submit this Government’s views in order that
                            they may be considered by the Council.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>